  "text": "Finally, note that the problem of low triple throughput can be solved with by using a lattice based additively homomorphic encryption with a massively vectorised message space. Essentially, we can use the same cryptosystem as in [CITATION_1] but with parameters which only assure additive homomorphism. The resulting cryptosystem is more efficient but must execute CDSZKMUL protocols. Hence, it is difficult to say whether this alternative is more efficient or not without practical experiments.",
